---
title: "Cross-sectional Analysis of Primary Care Clinics’ Policies, Practices, and Availability of Patient Support Services During the COVID-19 Pandemic"
collection: publications
category: published
permalink: /publication/2024-primary-care-covid19
excerpt: "This study examines how primary care clinics in Nebraska adapted their policies, practices, and patient support services during the COVID-19 pandemic."
date: 2024-03-05
venue: "BMC Health Services Research, 24, Article 279"
paperurl: "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12913-024-10660-6"
citation: "Ratnapradipa K.L., Wang R., Kabayundo J., Lavenant W.M., Nelson E., Ahuja M., Zhang Y., & Wang H. (2024). \"Cross-sectional Analysis of Primary Care Clinics’ Policies, Practices, and Availability of Patient Support Services During the COVID-19 Pandemic.\" <i>BMC Health Services Research</i>, 24, Article 279."
---
This cross-sectional study investigates how primary care clinics responded to the COVID-19 pandemic by adapting their internal policies, operational practices, and the availability of support services for patients. The findings offer insights into clinic-level strategies and ongoing challenges in maintaining accessible, equitable care.
